Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.75,0:00:18.39,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Piercing through the Macro sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.25,0:00:24.11,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,a thunderbolt strikes the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.95,0:00:29.81,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,To awaken us, the young mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.69,0:00:36.53,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,the Light struck
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.77,0:00:41.63,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Macross! Macross!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.97,0:00:48.24,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,The brave youths who arise
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.61,0:00:52.41,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,and fight to protect their loved ones
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.78,0:00:57.58,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Will set out on their journey\Nas the war rages on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.95,0:01:00.75,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you love me tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.12,0:01:06.09,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Slicing through the darkness they fly toward
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.46,0:01:12.30,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,that blue planet that shines in the distance
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.40,0:01:17.10,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Macross! Macross!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.61,0:01:23.64,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Macross!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.01,0:01:38.14,signM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(70,122)}CHINA TOWN
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.40,0:02:20.83,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there they go.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.41,0:02:23.18,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Must be nice. I wanna go too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.16,0:02:24.08,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.26,0:02:26.23,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,They're going to UN Forces\NHigh Command in Alaska,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.45,0:02:28.02,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,and it's not going to be fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.05,0:02:29.78,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a lot better off staying here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.97,0:02:31.04,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.05,0:02:32.61,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to get off the ship, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.38,0:02:36.24,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.98,0:02:42.51,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful, Colonel Maistroff.\NThat doorway's a little low.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.20,0:02:45.00,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.65,0:02:47.46,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a little late though.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.52,0:02:50.22,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be assuming command in\NCaptain Global's absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.25,0:02:51.58,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I was informed, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.02,0:03:07.04,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel! No smoking is allowed on the bridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.11,0:03:12.98,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I...I know that!\NI was just keeping it in my mouth!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.94,0:03:17.94,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Colonel, if you'll excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.67,0:03:21.66,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,My watch is over, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.55,0:03:24.08,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, very well, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.32,0:03:25.38,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.46,0:03:29.96,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going off to the Macross's return\Ncelebration by yourself, aren't you, Lieutenant?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.31,0:03:32.01,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, who can say?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.11,0:03:59.84,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! For the next three days and\Nnights, everyone, live it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.07,0:04:02.04,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,But Mr. Mayor, shouldn't we use\Nthat time to pack?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.07,0:04:05.35,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What're ya talkin' about?!\NWe can do that soon enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.50,0:04:07.10,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,The Macross has been our home\Nfor a while now,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.14,0:04:09.34,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,and soon it'll just be a nice memory!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.01,0:04:16.08,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess we do have a few\Ndays before we leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.23,0:04:17.20,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,'Sright!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.20,0:04:18.93,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,So ya gotta party! PARTY!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.78,0:04:24.15,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are these guys so happy\Njust to land on a planet?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.16,0:04:27.57,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Who cares?Anyway, thish\Nbooze they got ish great!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.71,0:04:29.30,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Start drinkin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.14,0:04:32.53,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you can really put that stuff away!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.97,0:04:35.71,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I can't take no notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.83,0:04:36.93,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.08,0:04:39.25,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, hell! We're takin' the day off!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.43,0:05:08.39,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Great. An unrivaled beauty\Nenters his room, and he just...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.36,0:05:11.89,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,You're cute when you're asleep,\NMr. Invincible Focker.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.32,0:05:17.38,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess I'll go take a shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.63,0:05:22.46,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Still got those lovely\Ncurves, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.62,0:05:24.72,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe a little worse for the wear though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.82,0:05:26.42,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that again?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.51,0:05:39.37,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Minmay!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.70,0:05:41.57,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Minmay!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.19,0:05:52.72,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, outta the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.58,0:05:57.14,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't even stop by my uncle's\Nto say hi anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.35,0:06:11.21,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.55,0:06:22.92,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like a lot of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.14,0:06:26.27,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but all my fans are\Nimportant to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.94,0:06:28.28,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that how it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.28,0:06:37.62,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.95,0:06:39.82,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a lot nicer now than\Nwhen we first met.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.57,0:06:43.00,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Y...You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.07,0:06:45.84,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Ichijo! I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.77,0:06:47.91,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.11,0:06:51.56,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be late coming back.\NI know you wanted to see your parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.56,0:06:53.86,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,but as your manager, I'm the one who\Nhas to balance your schedule and...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.98,0:06:57.28,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that.\NI'm not an amateur anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.10,0:07:00.32,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, as long as\Nyou understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.39,0:07:01.82,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going! Please stand back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.75,0:07:03.95,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. See you soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.55,0:07:26.47,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd forgotten what this felt like.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.88,0:07:28.78,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.80,0:07:29.67,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.68,0:08:12.41,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What's got you in such a good mood, Leader?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.72,0:08:14.56,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, it's you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.60,0:08:16.10,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What's THAT supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.11,0:08:16.91,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry 'bout that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.93,0:08:18.80,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be heading back now, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.13,0:08:23.87,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,And leave you and Minmay alone\Nto pursue your love.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.60,0:08:27.47,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Must be nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.19,0:08:29.58,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot! It's not like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.27,0:08:32.04,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to be shy about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.30,0:08:34.00,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, enjoy yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.59,0:08:43.76,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while since we were alone, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.79,0:08:44.49,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.93,0:08:48.63,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I can finally relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.65,0:08:50.75,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,But once I go back, I'll be\Nbusy all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.83,0:08:52.76,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have to make up the time I took off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.83,0:08:55.43,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't push yourself so hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.50,0:08:59.21,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see. As soon as I get back,\NI have that TV show taping...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.26,0:09:01.16,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Then there's a\Nlive appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.48,0:09:03.01,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,And then I'm going to be in a movie!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.69,0:09:08.10,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,My first movie! It's a lot of work too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.12,0:09:09.92,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'm recording an LP!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.29,0:09:11.98,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll send you one as a gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.29,0:09:13.29,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.92,0:09:18.56,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, can such a hard schedule\Nbe good for your health?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.82,0:09:21.09,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Minmay? Min...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.21,0:09:45.87,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,They must have put a lot of work into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.98,0:09:47.99,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, that's how far up we still are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.09,0:09:49.95,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,This shaft is a full six\Nkilometers deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.11,0:09:54.30,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, do you know about\Nthe Grand Cannon?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.08,0:09:55.98,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.03,0:09:58.28,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It's based on the main gun\Nof the Macross,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.32,0:10:00.59,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,and uses the Earth's gravitational field\Nas its energy source.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.64,0:10:03.27,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Work on it began seven or eight years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.49,0:10:07.69,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,This shaft is so huge because\Nit acts as the cannon's barrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.95,0:10:11.38,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,So everyone here lives inside a cannon?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.50,0:10:13.07,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you could put it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.26,0:10:15.50,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this your first time here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.54,0:10:18.00,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,No, my father brought me a few times.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.55,0:10:21.68,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,But he never took me down to the\Nbottom of the main shaft.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.23,0:10:27.96,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose not. Most officers aren't\Neven allowed there, let alone academy cadets.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.00,0:10:29.76,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.48,0:10:32.68,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.85,0:10:35.82,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. It's just, Admiral Hayase\Nis famous for being strict,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.18,0:10:38.56,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,so it's just like him to be no different\Nwith his own daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.67,0:10:41.41,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,My father? I don't know\Nwhat you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.71,0:10:46.24,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,He was my commander on the front line\Nduring the Unification Wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.31,0:10:51.02,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,He got into a disagreement with the higher-ups\Nover the distribution of our food supplies,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.09,0:10:54.03,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,so the idiot took a unit and had them\Nraid an allied warehouse!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.26,0:10:56.62,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,And you were in on it, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.95,0:11:06.48,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a nice face, Hayase.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.06,0:11:08.07,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.14,0:11:11.33,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't seen you smile since you\Nescaped from the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.96,0:11:17.73,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Things will be a little easier for us\Nonce we get High Command's support,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.96,0:11:21.76,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,but for that to happen, we're going to\Nhave to convince the top brass.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.81,0:11:25.34,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It may be rough on you, but I want you\Nto help me and try your hardest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.88,0:11:27.41,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. I'll give it my all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.49,0:11:29.55,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.62,0:11:37.09,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,No smoking is allowed in the capsule.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.14,0:11:38.87,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Please refrain from your tobacco.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.10,0:11:40.67,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Of all the... Here too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.75,0:11:43.21,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,First Shammy and now this machine!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.83,0:11:48.06,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Captain, you're worried about the others\Non the Macross, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.09,0:11:48.99,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.26,0:11:53.03,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,You always take out your pipe when\Nyou're worried about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.16,0:11:55.86,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? I never noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.35,0:11:58.52,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I don't think there will be\Nany attacks for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.62,0:12:00.78,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,We've seen that the enemy's chain\Nof command is in disarray.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.71,0:12:03.63,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,But how long will that last?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.42,0:12:06.22,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Not very long, I'm afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.30,0:12:28.83,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Minmay, wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.63,0:13:01.83,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while, Global.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.86,0:13:03.76,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Not since the launching of the Macross.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.14,0:13:04.62,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.65,0:13:06.01,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Same for you, Captain Hayase.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.21,0:13:07.60,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Admiral.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.07,0:13:10.34,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Both of you, take your seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.37,0:13:14.24,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, shall we begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.43,0:13:18.13,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,Having already received Global's report,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.33,0:13:21.57,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,the military officials began their\Ncross-examination.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.59,0:13:26.83,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,And immediately, their responses made\NMisa and Global painfully aware
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.11,0:13:30.10,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,of the deficiencies in their observations.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.50,0:13:41.89,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Smell that salt air!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.09,0:13:46.15,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing's changed at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.21,0:13:48.91,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Good old Yokohama!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.95,0:13:50.62,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, everyone's staring.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.78,0:13:54.55,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmmph. I take you to Harbor Viewing Park on a\Nlovely day, and you're just spoiling the mood!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.78,0:13:56.12,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.41,0:13:59.60,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Look! That's the New Marine Tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.79,0:14:04.68,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 900 meters tall, and when it was built\Nit was the tallest thing in the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.13,0:14:06.55,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same age as I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.53,0:14:08.23,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.16,0:14:10.96,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Be more impressed!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.10,0:14:28.10,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see, there's the Yokohama\NDai-Hanten Restaurant,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.21,0:14:30.01,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,and there's the Canton Saikan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.06,0:14:31.73,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad! Nothing's changed!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.80,0:14:33.80,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't even look like Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.85,0:14:35.88,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why it's called Chinatown.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.86,0:14:38.86,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Past the Kainan Hanten...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.40,0:14:40.42,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.80,0:14:41.53,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.56,0:14:42.43,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.10,0:14:46.67,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness! My home's still here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.91,0:14:49.50,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It hasn't even been a year, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.82,0:14:52.72,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It feels like it's been ten already!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.74,0:14:53.93,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.90,0:14:59.59,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Minmay!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.19,0:15:03.85,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon! Just c'mon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.49,0:15:03.85,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&\1a&H00&}What is it, Chin?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.72,0:15:06.16,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.46,0:15:07.83,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Minmay!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.78,0:15:11.02,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.06,0:15:12.59,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.59,0:15:15.86,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you'd been killed long ago\Nin the Unification Wars!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.06,0:15:17.83,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,The Unification Wars?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.57,0:15:20.50,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.56,0:15:23.36,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Hikaru. He saved my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.47,0:15:25.94,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.01,0:15:28.08,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's all right. You're embarrassing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.16,0:15:30.73,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Minmay! How could you make\Nus worry like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.83,0:15:33.02,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you send word that\Nyou were still alive?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.56,0:15:40.09,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Global, Captain Hayase...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.15,0:15:44.09,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't have expected this\Nfrom either of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.21,0:15:46.78,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,First of all, if the enemy is as\Npowerful as you claim,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.80,0:15:49.00,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,why was the Macross allowed to return?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.15,0:15:51.92,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I detailed our reasoning\Nin the report.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.98,0:15:55.17,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if that report is true,\Nit contains several gaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.21,0:15:55.17,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&\1a&H00&}But it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.37,0:15:57.24,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough, Captain Hayase!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.67,0:15:59.70,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Admiral!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.70,0:16:04.33,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, will you grant my previous request?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.46,0:16:08.30,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,The negotiation plan and the relocation\Nof the 56,000 refugees?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.61,0:16:11.95,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll take that up in our deliberations.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.86,0:16:16.72,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Captain, why are they doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.40,0:16:20.07,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think we've seen their\Ntrue intentions yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.26,0:16:21.86,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.87,0:16:25.64,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,They're also politicians, Hayase.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.00,0:16:30.60,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,If we spend all this time deliberating, do you\Nthink we can get anything done in time?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.03,0:16:39.06,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,OUT OF THE QUESTION!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.63,0:16:43.53,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! You only just got back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.65,0:16:45.95,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't go be a singer on some battleship!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.98,0:16:48.12,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be like being a comfort woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.26,0:16:50.76,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Comfort woman?\NTalk about old-fashioned!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.79,0:16:53.50,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I don't care what you say,\NI'm going back to the Macross!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.67,0:16:55.33,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not gonna blow this chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.36,0:16:56.60,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,No! No!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.88,0:16:58.58,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.73,0:17:02.93,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I am! I'm on TV in the Macross,\Nand I'm about to do a record!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.93,0:17:04.94,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm even going to be in a movie soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.09,0:17:06.11,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Hikaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.42,0:17:10.56,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would we believe a made-up\Nstory like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.58,0:17:12.00,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.63,0:17:14.44,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,You're our only child.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.82,0:17:17.69,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Who will run the restaurant\Nwhen we, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.53,0:17:20.80,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What about you, son?\NWould you settle down with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.16,0:17:23.76,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?! Well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.78,0:17:24.81,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.92,0:17:28.16,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,You're making Hikaru uncomfortable!\NOur relationship isn't like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.01,0:17:32.74,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,And anyway, I can't betray my\Ntens of thousands of fans!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.09,0:17:35.29,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a professional now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.55,0:17:37.18,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,You're still going on about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.22,0:17:38.59,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.75,0:17:42.44,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,You said it was important.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.70,0:17:43.83,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Minmay!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.12,0:17:46.76,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaifun, it's you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.77,0:17:48.53,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I dreaming?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.00,0:17:53.74,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaifun, I never expected to see you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.84,0:17:55.90,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, after I joined the peace movement,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.94,0:17:59.80,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't stand being near the Macross\Nanymore, so I left home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.16,0:18:03.80,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I was going to come back to see Mom and Dad,\Nbut I stopped getting any mail from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.87,0:18:06.26,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I found out that the\Nisland was destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.92,0:18:08.34,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It was really something.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.10,0:18:11.27,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm glad at least you're\Nstill alive, Minmay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.31,0:18:13.78,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Your mom and dad are just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.96,0:18:15.36,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?! Where are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.49,0:18:16.42,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Aboard the Macross.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.60,0:18:17.45,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,The Macross?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.48,0:18:18.58,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.86,0:18:19.96,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.99,0:18:21.19,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.81,0:18:23.31,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me introduce you, Hikaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.37,0:18:26.24,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my cousin Lynn Kaifun.\NHe's like a big brother to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.02,0:18:28.39,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Good to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.57,0:18:31.14,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,This is 1st Lieutenant Hikaru Ichijo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.21,0:18:33.91,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a fighter pilot aboard the Macross,\Nand he saved my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.83,0:18:36.29,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Hikaru Ichijo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.69,0:18:37.79,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so that's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.82,0:18:40.01,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Soldiers are expected to help\Nus civilians, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.17,0:18:43.81,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I guess I can go ahead and say thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.83,0:18:47.02,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,No! He wasn't a soldier when he saved me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.11,0:18:49.81,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so you joined up later?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.92,0:18:50.92,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.93,0:18:52.32,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,And what's so great about the military?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.95,0:19:00.71,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,They sure are taking their time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.94,0:19:03.37,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive the delay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.42,0:19:07.19,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,We've analyzed your report and have determined\Nthat it is credible to a certain extent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.11,0:19:09.31,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.66,0:19:13.22,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,However, contact or negotiations with\Nthe enemy are out of the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.29,0:19:15.56,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,But attempting to continue hostilities\Nwith them is just...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.71,0:19:17.51,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,You still don't seem to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.61,0:19:22.85,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,The Zentradi way of thinking is completely\Ndifferent from our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.96,0:19:29.03,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if your theory is correct and their\Nancestors were similar to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.38,0:19:32.78,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,they are now quite different, Commodore Global.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.33,0:19:37.76,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Handled incorrectly, peace talks with these\Naliens could very well have adverse effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.99,0:19:42.56,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood. What about letting the\N56,000 civilians off of the Macross?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.71,0:19:46.58,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,They've all been declared dead.\NWe can't allow them to leave the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.94,0:19:47.98,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.98,0:19:49.15,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.19,0:19:52.99,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you think we could tell the public\Nwe're at war with aliens?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.12,0:19:55.12,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,It would have thrown the entire\NEarth into a panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.32,0:19:59.61,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,After the Macross launched into space,\Nwe took control of the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.67,0:20:03.22,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,We said that the Macross had been attacked by\Nguerillas, remnants of the anti-UN Forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.25,0:20:07.86,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,They destroyed South Ataria Island, and the\NMacross launched on its test flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.11,0:20:13.03,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think we can let 56,000 ghosts\Nwho know the truth go free?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.91,0:20:14.93,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.66,0:20:18.36,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,If we try to keep them on board now,\Nit will cause a riot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.43,0:20:20.92,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,After all they've been through, they've finally\Nmade it back home, and now...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.97,0:20:24.31,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Keeping them in line is your responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.78,0:20:31.92,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, if your report is correct and the\Nenemy is so interested in civilians
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.18,0:20:36.62,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,then the Macross, which is full of civilians,\Nshould occupy their attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.67,0:20:37.46,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.49,0:20:40.13,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Continue to keep the aliens occupied,\Nas you've been doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.19,0:20:43.32,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,While you're doing that, we'll be\Npreparing our counterattack.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.42,0:20:45.62,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I know it's risky, but you have to\Nbuy us some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.86,0:20:48.93,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Father, you're asking too much!\NAt least let the civilians...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.96,0:20:50.93,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave our relationship out of this, Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.98,0:20:53.58,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,We may be father and daughter,\Nbut here we are both soldiers!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.84,0:20:59.08,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy could ignore the Macross\Nand attack the Earth directly!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.46,0:21:02.18,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Our analysis shows there is little\Nchance of that happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.28,0:21:04.81,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll receive more detailed instructions later.\NThat is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.60,0:21:20.95,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Hayase, aren't you going to speak with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.06,0:21:23.55,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,He is your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.43,0:21:28.60,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to see him. Not now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.32,0:21:39.42,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,This is going nowhere. Minmay's mind\Nis made up. Why not let her go?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.62,0:21:41.42,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, Kaifun!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.52,0:21:42.59,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Kaifun!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.66,0:21:46.26,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked you to talk to her because you\Ntwo have always gotten along.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.48,0:21:48.41,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,But now you've just taken her side!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.03,0:21:51.16,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,However, I intend to go with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.22,0:21:55.08,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I get to be with Kaifun! This is the best!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.45,0:21:57.39,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I didn't think of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.54,0:21:59.43,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't be so worried if\NKaifun was with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.04,0:22:01.24,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Just leave everything to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.23,0:22:23.70,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"Misa, I'm sure you're angry with my decision,"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.71,0:22:26.98,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"but as a ranking official of the UN Forces High\NCommand, it was the only decision to make."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.08,0:22:28.82,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"Please try to understand."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.90,0:22:32.13,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"And now, as your\Nfather, I have a request."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.39,0:22:34.90,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"Leave the Macross at once."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.93,0:22:37.16,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"I'll make whatever arrangements are necessary."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.17,0:22:40.53,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"I can't bear to have my daughter\Nin such a dangerous place..."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.72,0:22:48.76,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,So you don't have a single girlfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.33,0:22:51.70,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope! I've been dumped the world over.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.09,0:22:54.46,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd be jealous if you ever got a girlfriend!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.21,0:22:57.67,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What, you want me to be alone\Nfor the rest of my life?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.16,0:22:59.89,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I'm saying...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.94,0:23:00.95,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,What, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.96,0:23:02.08,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Never you mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.95,0:23:04.09,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.33,0:23:05.96,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,We're already carrying more weight\Nthan we should be,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.01,0:23:07.40,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,so would you mind settling\Ndown back there?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.26,0:23:10.89,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you trying to act all big, Hikaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.11,0:23:12.53,Macross1,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.75,0:23:17.82,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,Having set foot on the Earth for\Nthe first time in quite a while
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.92,0:23:20.79,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,and still puzzling over the\Nunexpected twists of fate,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.89,0:23:24.55,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,they hurry back with mixed feelings\Nin their hearts...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.49,0:23:28.36,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,to their home aboard the Macross.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.10,0:23:34.95,signM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(87,107)}Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.10,0:23:34.95,signM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(339,456)}Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.86,0:23:41.53,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,Minmay's cousin Lynn Kaifun\Nhas returned to a home
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.68,0:23:44.71,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,that has been transplanted\Naboard the Macross.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.19,0:23:48.29,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,This somewhat unusual passenger\Ncauses new troubles
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.41,0:23:53.41,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,not just for Hikaru, but for everyone\Naboard the Macross.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.92,0:23:57.55,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Super Dimension\NFortress Macross:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.62,0:23:59.52,narration,,0000,0000,0000,,"KUNG-FU DANDY"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.47,0:24:01.92,signM,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(90,137)}KUNG-FU DANDY
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.84,0:24:22.40,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't follow it anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.73,0:24:29.03,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,The shadow you cast as you run away
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.87,0:24:36.07,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,We all keep running until the end
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.22,0:24:43.58,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,But we still can't see the goal
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.80,0:24:50.07,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,What awaits us after today?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.26,0:24:55.72,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,What awaits us beyond tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.78,0:25:03.95,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,Even now, I keep running toward
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.01,0:25:15.15,songM,,0000,0000,0000,,The light that shines so far away
